## Routing Patterns

### Path Structure

```
/<resource>/<id>[/<sub-resource>/<sub-id>]
```

Examples:
- `/products/123`
- `/orders/456/items`
- `/user/profile`
- `/search?q=shoes`

### Router Implementation

- [ ] Central router or navigation handler for all deep link paths
- [ ] Path parameters extracted and validated
- [ ] Query parameters supported for filters, search
- [ ] Invalid paths redirect to home or 404 screen
- [ ] Log deep link opens for analytics and debugging

### Example Router (Pseudocode)

```swift
func handleDeepLink(url: URL) -> Bool {
  guard let components = URLComponents(url: url, resolvingAgainstBaseURL: false),
        let path = components.path else { return false }
  let segments = path.split(separator: "/").map(String.init)
  switch (segments.first, segments.dropFirst()) {
  case ("products", [let id]): navigateToProduct(id: id); return true
  case ("orders", [let id]): navigateToOrder(id: id); return true
  default: return false
  }
}
```

