## Fallback to Web

### When App Not Installed

- [ ] Same URL works in browser (Universal Links / App Links)
- [ ] Web page shows "Open in App" with store links
- [ ] Store links use correct scheme (itms-apps, market)
- [ ] After install, deferred deep link restores context if supported

### When App Installed

- [ ] Link opens app directly (no intermediate web page)
- [ ] User is taken to correct in-app destination
- [ ] Back navigation behaves correctly

---

## Deferred Deep Links

### Use Case

User clicks link on device without app installed. After installing and opening, user should land on the intended content.

### Implementation Options

| Provider | Notes |
|----------|-------|
| Branch.io | Full-featured; attribution |
| Adjust | Attribution + deferred |
| Firebase Dynamic Links | Deprecated Aug 2025 |
| Custom | Store click ID in cookie; pass to app on first launch |

### Requirements

- [ ] Click ID or fingerprint stored (cookie, redirect)
- [ ] On first app launch, check for pending deferred link
- [ ] Fetch link data from server using click ID
- [ ] Navigate to destination
- [ ] Clear deferred state after handling
- [ ] Timeout (e.g., 24 hours) for stale deferred links

---

## Attribution

### Use Cases

- Campaign tracking (which ad drove install)
- Referral tracking (which user invited)
- Content sharing (which post was shared)

### Best Practices

- [ ] Use dedicated link parameters (utm_source, utm_campaign, or custom)
- [ ] Persist attribution on first launch
- [ ] Do not overwrite attribution after install (first-touch)
- [ ] Respect user privacy; do not share PII in links
- [ ] Document attribution parameters in analytics

